\subsection{Induced structures and factoring through maps}


Let ${\boldsymbol{K}}$ be a topological ${\mathcal{L}}$-structure, let $A$ be a zero-dimensional, second countable, compact space and let $f:K\to A$ be a continuous surjection. Notice that there is a unique topological ${\mathcal{L}}$-structure ${\boldsymbol{A}}$ on domain $A$ that renders $f$ an epimorphism. We call this structure ${\boldsymbol{A}}$, the structure \emph{induced by the map} $f$.

Let $f:{\boldsymbol{K}}\to {\boldsymbol{A}}, h:{\boldsymbol{K}}\to{\boldsymbol{B}}$ be epimorphisms. We say that $f$ \emph{factors through} $h$ if there is an epimorphism $f_h:{\boldsymbol{B}}\to{\boldsymbol{A}}$ such that $f_h\circ h= f$.

\begin{lm}\label{factors through lemma}
Let ${\boldsymbol{A}},{\boldsymbol{B}}$ and ${\boldsymbol{K}}$ be topological ${\mathcal{L}}$-structures with ${\boldsymbol{A}},{\boldsymbol{B}}$ finite. Let also $f:{\boldsymbol{K}}\to{\boldsymbol{A}}$ and  $g:{\boldsymbol{K}}\to{\boldsymbol{B}}$ be epimorphisms. Then there is a finite topological ${\mathcal{L}}$-structure ${\boldsymbol{C}}$ and an epimorphism $h:{\boldsymbol{K}}\to{\boldsymbol{C}}$ such that both $f$ and $g$ factor through $h$. 
\end{lm}
\begin{proof}
Let $C=(\Delta_0,\ldots,\Delta_{n-1})$ a clopen partition of $K$ whose every entry $\Delta_i$ is a (nonempty) set of the form $f^{-1}(a)\cap g^{-1}(b)$, where $a\in A$ and $b\in B$. Let $h:K\to C$ be the inclusion map, i.e, $h(x)=\Delta_i$ if and only if $x\in\Delta_i$. This map is a continuous surjection, so, it induces a structure ${\boldsymbol{C}}$ on domain $C$. It is immediate now that both $f$ and $g$ factor through $h$.   
